
[1]vehement

   VE'HEMENT, a. [L. vehemens.]

   1. Violent; acting with great force; furious; very forcible; as a
   vehement wind; a vehement torrent; a vehement fire or heat.

   2. Very ardent; very eager or urgent; very fervent; as a vehement
   affection or passion; vehement desire; vehement eloquence.
